<sn><md>## Physical Geography vs Human Geography

| Aspect           | Physical Geography                                     | Human Geography                                                                        |
| ---------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Definition**   | Study of the Earth's natural features and processes    | Study of human activities and their relationship with the environment                  |
| **Focus**        | Landforms, climate, vegetation, soils, water bodies    | Population, settlements, economy, culture, political systems                           |
| **Purpose**      | Understanding natural environment and processes        | Understanding human behavior, societal patterns, and interactions with the environment |
| **Methods**      | Observation, mapping, remote sensing, field surveys    | Census, surveys, statistical analysis, GIS                                             |
| **Examples**     | Mountains, rivers, deserts, earthquakes, climate zones | Cities, agriculture, industries, migration, cultural regions                           |
| **Relationship** | Provides the physical setting for human activities     | Influences and modifies the physical environment                                       |
</md></sn>